annotationA: Pale is a tyrosine hydroxylase, the first and rate-limiting step in the synthesis of dopamine (and eventually, melanin). Dopamine has critical roles in system development
annotationB: Scavenger receptor acting in neural tissue and majority of rhodopsin is absent, isoform A; Scavenger receptor activity.
